<a id="top"> </a><h1>Full-time Research and Teaching Position (Wissenschaftlicher Mitarbeiter), University of Cologne, Germany</h1>
<p>
The department of philosophy at the University of Cologne, Germany, 
invites applications  for a full-time research and teaching position 
(Wissenschaftlicher Mitarbeiter) at the Chair of Practical Philosophy 
and Ethics in the Life Sciences (Prof. Wilfried Hinsch). Appointment 
will be on a fixed-term three-year basis, with the possibility of 
renewal. The annual salary will be in the range of 37.300–53.950,-&euro; 
(E 13 TV-L), depending on qualification and experience. Working hours: 
39,83 per week.
</p>
<p>
Responsibilities include independent research and teaching as well as 
contributing to the development of an interdisciplinary centre for 
ethics at the University of Cologne.
</p>
<p>
The successful applicant will have a degree and PhD (or equivalent) in 
Philosophy. Required are sound knowledge of the philosophy of language 
and the philosophy of science, and specific expertise and research 
interests in both empirical ethics (metaethics, moral psychology, social 
anthropology, evolutionary biology) and applied practical ethics (in the 
field of the life sciences). Competences in at least one of these areas 
should be documented by the PhD dissertation.
</p>
<p>
The University of Cologne is an equal opportunity employer in compliance 
with the German disability laws. Applications from women and disabled 
persons are particularly welcome.
</p>
